Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 81
Edition:
Quote: <i>pakapoo ticket, look/marked like a </i>something confusing or incomprehensible; from Chinese lottery ticket with its (to Europeans) incomprehensible markings. Housie-type game played in illegal gambling and opium dens such as those in Haining Street, Wellington; eg `This ruddy exam's marked like a pakapoo ticket!'
